      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're saying religious belief always wins, no matter what the cost. if a group uses their religion to justify something that's actually harmful or discriminatory to others, shouldn't the law step in to prevent that harm? i just don't see how a society can function if everyone can just opt out of the rules they don't like based on what they believe. isn't there a limit to that?",
